possible for an administrator to manually edit the /etc/passwd file and change the UID
field.

Rationale:

Users must be assigned unique UIDs for accountability and to ensure appropriate access
protections."
      solution    : "Based on the results of the audit script, establish unique UIDs and review all files owned by
the shared UIDs to determine which UID they are supposed to belong to."
      reference   : "800-171|3.5.5,800-171|3.5.6,800-53|IA-4,CN-L3|7.1.2.7(b),CN-L3|8.1.4.1(a),CSCv6|16,CSCv7|16,CSF|PR.AC-1,ITSG-33|IA-4,LEVEL|1S,NESA|T5.5.2,NIAv2|AM14a,SWIFT-CSCv1|5"
